												﻿
PRIVACY NOTICE BANAMEX
At Banco Nacional de México, S.A., member of  Grupo Financiero Banamex (henceforth “Banamex”),Tarjetas Banamex, S.A. de C.V., Sofom E.R. (henceforth “Tarjetas Banamex”) and Servicios Financieros Soriana, S.A.P.I. de C.V., Sofom E.R. (henceforth “Soriban”) we are certain that our main asset are our customers and to protect their information,  we enforce guidelines, policies, procedures and privacy programs. 

As a Banamex, Banamex Cards and Soriban customer, you can be certain that your information is protected by the use, application and management of high physical and administrative security techniques.


In addition, on July 5th 2010 in the Official Gazette of Federal Law on Protection of Personal Data Held by Private Parties (El Diario Oficial de la Federación la Ley Federal de Protección de Datos Personales en Posesión de Particulares) (henceforth "Ley"),whose provisions clearly contribute to our goal of protecting your personal data. You can access the Ley content through the Federal Government website, conducted by the Interior Ministry (Secretaria de Governación)and the Chamber of Deputies from the Parliament, whose web addresses are:  http://www.ordenjuridico.gob.mx and http://www.diputados.gob.mx


Under the above, we inform you that in compliance with our Privacy Program and Law, all the data obtained under transactions you request or celebrate with Banamex , Banamex Cards and Soriban will be treated confidentially through systems and schemes provided for this purpose.
Responsible for the processing of personal data:


Banco Nacional de México, S.A., Member of  Grupo Financiero Banamex (henceforth “Banamex”), Tarjetas Banamex, S.A. de C.V., Sofom E.R., Member of  Grupo Financiero Banamex (henceforth “Tarjetas Banamex”) and/or  Servicios Financieros Soriana, S.A.P.I. de C.V., Sofom E.R. Member of  Grupo Financiero Banamex (henceforth “Soriban”), are the ones responsible of obtaining and treating your personal data. Each of whom is responsible for all the data in his role as Responsible..
Responsibles address:


Banamex, Tarjetas Banamex and Soriban, indicate that the individual address for the purposes of the privacy notice is, Avenida 16 de Septiembre número 73, ground floor, neighbourhood Centro, Suburb Cuauhtémoc, ZIP code 06000, México, Distrito Federal (CDMX).
Personal data processing purposes:


The personal data collected BY Banamex, Banamex and Soriban cards will be used to meet the following purposes:


a) Purpose indispensable for the fulfillment of the juridical relationship (i) To confirm your identity and veracity of the information provided, including beneficiaries, references, required solidarity, guarantees or sureties, as applicable. (Ii) To integrate files, databases and systems necessary to carry out the relevant banking. (Iii) To complete KYC provisions and prevention of money laundering, whether for Banamex or their affiliates or subsidiaries that are part of the same financial group, as provided by law respectively. (Iv) to maintain the legal relationship generated. (V) To claim prize, scoring systems and other loyalty programs, as well as in your case, collection processes that could result from the legal relationship. (Vi) To carry out feasibility analysis and credit risk; and comply with regulations, policies and measures of physical security and civil protection, such as systems video surveillance, access to facilities and restricted areas. (Vii) To allow access to any of the buildings in which offices or branches are located.


b) Purpose not indispensable for the fulfillment of the juridical relation.- Additionally, they may use your personal data for the following secondary objectives: (i) marketing, advertising and market research; (Ii) provide, where appropriate, other banking or financial products themselves or any of its affiliates, subsidiaries, holding companies, associated companies, brokers or company members of Grupo Financiero Banamex; (Iii) send promotions of other goods or services related with said bank or financial products; (Iv) to inform you or invite you to participate in our non-profit social commitment activities that aim to promote the development of people through educational, social, ecological and cultural projects; and (v) for analysis statistician, generating information models and / or current profiles and predictive behavior. Participate in surveys, sweepstakes and promotions.
Personal data which may be collected and processed:


Banamex , Banamex Cards and Soriban will collect personal data necessary to fulfill your request of a product, banking or financial services as well as to formalize their respective recruitment, accordance with the purposes described above .


Personal data categories to be collected and treated are subject to:
( i ) identification data ( ii )contact data; ( Iii )physical characteristics data ( iv ) biometrics limited to fingerprint, voice recognition, facial identification features ; ( V ) business data; 
( Vi) academic or professional data; ( Vii ) migration data ; ( Viii ) economic and / or financial data ; and ( ix ) health status data(Classified as sensitive data) ; in the cases mentioned in ( viii ) and ( ix ) shall be obtained by separate express consent and / or express written consent as appropriate.

Banamex , Banamex Cards and Soriban may conduct investigations and actions they deem necessary , in order to check through third parties contracted to do so, agency or authority, the accuracy of the data they were provided.

Means to limit the scope(use or disclosure)of your personal data:

You or your duly accredited legal representative may at any time object to the processing of your personal data for purposes that are not essential to the legal relationship that gave origin to the contracted or requested service, indicating it in the box called.

"Usage Information Authorization" contained in the application for the product or service subscribed with Banamex Cards, Banamex or Soriban , or through the procedure for the exercise of ARCO rights , which is detailed in this Privacy Notice.
Personal data transfer:


Banamex, Banamex Cards and Soriban may transfer your personal data to Mexican or foreigners third parties when the transfer: (i) is provided for in a law or treaty in which Mexico is a party; (Ii)it is necessary for the prevention or the medical diagnosis, the provision of health care, treatment doctor or service management (iii) be made to holding companies, subsidiaries or affiliates under the common control of Banamex, Banamex Cards or Soriban, a parent company or any society of the same group responsible operating under the same processes and internal policies; (Iv) necessary by virtue of a contract concluded or to be concluded in the interest of the owner, by Banamex, Banamex Cards Soriban and a third party; (V) if it is necessary or legally required to safeguard the public interest or for the enforcement or administration of justice; (Vi) if it is required for the establishment, exercise or defense of rights in judicial proceedings; and (vii) if it is necessary for the maintenance or fulfillment of a legal relationship between Banamex, Banamex Cards or Soriban and the holder.
ARCO rights:


You or your duly authorized legal representative may limit the use or circulation of your personal data, as well as exercise, if applicable, the rights of Access, Rectification, Cancelation or Opposition established by the Law through the form that Banamex, Tarjetas Banamex or Soriban provide for these purposes, which should be accompanied with the documents accrediting the identity of the account-holder (official identification with photograph) or, in its case, the representation of the account holder in terms of common regulation, submit it in any Banamex branch, which will take your request to the personal data department of Banamex, Tarjetas Banamex and Soriban to process the requests of account holders for the exercise of ARCO rights within a period no longer than 20 business days from receipt. It is important to mention that the exercise of any of the mentioned rights is not a prior requisite nor does it impede the exercise of another right.


You can get the form to exercise ARCO rights by clicking here or through any Banamex branch. The answer to requests that meet the above requirements may be notified via email ( if the email address is provided ) from the  datpersona@banamex.com, by courier or fax , coupled to be available in any Banamex branch with proof of identity by any means noted above. For security reasons, no requests to exercise ARCO rights will be addressed if sent to the above e-mail address, since through such means it is impossible to prove the personality of the petitioner.

Also, we inform you that you are entitled to initiate a procedure for Rights Protection at the Federal Institute of Access to Information and Data Protection (www.ifai.gob.mx) within 15 (Fifteen) business days following the receipt response date sent by Banamex, Banamex Cards or Soriban, or from the deadline of twenty (20) working days from the date of receipt of your request to exercise rights and had not received any answer. 
Consent Revocation:


You may revoke the consent granted to Banamex, Banamex Cards Soriban for the processing of personal data, always and when data are not needed to complete the essential purposes described above, within the limits set by law and consistent with the obligations set out. However, it is important to note that not all cases can accommodate your request or terminate the use immediately, since it is possible that by any legal obligation we keep trying to require your personal data in the preprocessing to lock appropriately.

For the revocation to have effect, you may ask our Call Centre or go to any branch for the respective format, through which we exclude, within 35 (Thirty five) days from receipt of this format, the purpose of our campaigns marketers, advertising or commercial prospecting, with proof of their identity or, where appropriate, the legal representative, which shall meet without any additional requirement and therefore, no need to come later for some response.

Additionally, we inform you that you can enroll in the Users Public Registry (REUS for it Spanish initials), which contains information from users of the financial system who do not want to be bothered with advertising and promotions by financial institutions in their marketing practices, advertising and commercial prospecting, through the website of the National Commission for the Users Protection and Defense of Financial Services (Condusef, for its Spanish initials) whose address is http://www.condusef.gob.mx
Privacy Notice Modifications:


This privacy notice may undergo modifications, changes or updates resulting from new Legal requirements; Banamex, Banamex Cards or Soriban own products or service’s needs; privacy practices; changes in our business model, or for other reasons.

Any change to this privacy notice will be notified through any of the following means: a written statement sent to your home or delivered at any Banamex branch; a message contained in your statement; a message sent to your email or to your mobile phone; a message released through www.banamex.com or any electronic means you use to enter into transactions with Banamex , Banamex Cards or Soriban ; or through Posts at Banamex branches or in newspapers of general circulation.
Banamex , Banamex and Soriban Cards Commitment:


Banamex , Banamex Cards and Soriban are convinced that the main asset is our customers,that is why we apply physical and technical security and guidelines controls, policies, privacy procedures and programs to protect your information.


Update on July 2016.

      
		
		
	
	
	
	
			
		
	
		
  





